{"tid":1379012,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"[核彈] 有居美學者打算眾籌喺美國登報，敦促國會盡快通過「香港人權及民主法」","createTime":"2019-07-28T17:22:02.000Z","updateTime":"2019-07-30T10:01:23.000Z","uid":36592,"like":263,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":68,"replies":[{"pid":"400df052880890c22900159976d92579bb26b19a","tid":1379012,"uid":36592,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-28T17:22:02.000Z","msg":"Post 1<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/scientisthk2usa/photos/a.2136342016681918/2286414951674623/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fscientisthk2usa%2Fphotos%2Fa.2136342016681918%2F2286414951674623%2F&d=2WRE5dcwgWUU%2Ft06b4Zyywg0DHywPMniAnH04N%2BeXdM%3D&h=5068de65\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/scientisthk2usa/photos/a.2136342016681918/2286414951674623/</a><br />\n相信這一個半月以來，大家都參與過不少聯署行動。針對美國的聯署，似乎很多都未有從美國角度出發，尤其香港如何影響美國利益一點。這些年來，我學到的重要一課是，如果想別人信任你，你就要 speak their language。<br />\n<br />\n是故我正考慮發起聯署，以美國國家安全為由，敦促國會盡快通過「香港人權及民主法」，並感謝國會及國務院對香港的支持，對侵總統的不作為表示遺憾。以下是草稿，如果有 100+ likes+loves，並收到足夠意見，就會正式發起聯署；如果有 500+ 簽署，就會正式提交。<strong><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">為加強效用，從美國人角度出發，暫擬只開放予居美港人（包括學生及其他未持移民簽證者），以及持美國護照者參與。</span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\nPost 2<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/scientisthk2usa/photos/a.2136342016681918/2286779141638204/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fscientisthk2usa%2Fphotos%2Fa.2136342016681918%2F2286779141638204%2F&d=2WRE5dcwgWUU%2Ft06b4Zyywg0DHywPMniAnH04N%2BeXdM%3D&h=b2520ed4\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/scientisthk2usa/photos/a.2136342016681918/2286779141638204/</a><br />\n想不到昨晚一小時內就已經超過 100+ likes，聯署事在必行，先感謝大家的支持和參與。Together we can bring about change.<br />\n<br />\n在就聯署信件內容作最後定案前，我想先討論一下聯署方式，昨晚的帖也約略討論過一下。請大家投票：<br />\n<br />\n😮 使用網上平台自動發送電郵與你的參眾兩院議員<br />\n😄 買 WSJ 或 WaPo 全版廣告<br />\n😢 both<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\"><span style=\"color: red;\">截圖是 WSJ 的廣告收費，全版廣告盛惠 $277,200，必須眾籌；本人沒有連登 account，需要各位協助設立眾籌平台並直接過數。不過之前 G20 的時候，大家也在短時間內眾籌了數百萬賣廣告，希望今次也可以。</span></span></strong><br />\n<br />\nWaPo 的廣告收費表寫得有點兒模糊，我已電郵過去作進一步查詢。另外，有網友提議的 US News and World Report，平常在酒店都會供應、厚度較薄的報紙，則收 $30,000。登報的話，會列出聯署者的姓名、城巿、州份。<br />\n<br />\n如果是使用網上平台，程序上當然最簡單，也可以直接送到議員郵箱。但能見度必然較登報為低，而且我所知道的兩個網上聯署平台 (actionnetwork 跟 change) 都有左翼背景，共和黨可能不喜歡；反之若使用右翼平台，民主黨也可能不高興。<br />\n<br />\n請大家投票，結果會按投票結果及大家提供的理據決定。當然如果眾籌的話，也要得到足夠的支持。"},{"pid":"8cf707e087d2863f002b54ed5c50feffb0432984","tid":1379012,"uid":36592,"like":24,"dislike":0,"score":24,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-07-28T17:22:22.000Z","msg":"至於信件內容，感謝網友 Jiaway Hwang 就我昨晚的初稿作出修訂，添加了許多重要的論點。另有一好友表示今晚會再給予一些意見。經本人略作修改並添加標題後，暫時如下：<br />\n<br />\n===<br />\n<br />\nStand up for Hong Kong now for the sake of US national security!<br />\n<br />\nDear Americans,<br />\n<br />\nWe are writing to you as fellow Americans with family and business ties to Hong Kong. We, along with Hongkongers currently residing in the US, are deeply troubled by the latest developments in the autonomous city, home to at least 85,000 US citizens. This started with the Hong Kong government&rsquo;s unilateral introduction of an amendment to the autonomous city's Extradition Law, which would have allowed authorities to extradite anyone accused of criminal behavior by any Chinese authorities, regardless of the person&rsquo;s nationality (including Americans), to China without due process. Already, many of our Canadian neighbors have been arrested in China in retaliation of Canada&rsquo;s cooperation in building the case against Huawei with US authorities. Imagine what would have happened, and will happen, had the law been passed.<br />\n<br />\nWhile the proposed legislation has been &quot;suspended&quot;, the Hong Kong government has thus far refused to withdraw the bill. Worse, it has stepped up its suppression of largely peaceful protesters. Indeed, there have been substantiated accusations of the Hong Kong Police Force colluding with gang members to carry out indiscriminate and brutal attacks on the city's residents, as has been widely reported by major news outlets around the world.<br />\n<br />\nThese acts, however heinous, might seem irrelevant to the US at first glance, but a free and democratic Hong Kong is vital to US interests, especially when it comes to national security. Hongkongers are a freedom-loving people and we have long been strong believers of the US-based system. Young people in Hong Kong, having seen and experienced China&rsquo;s abuses firsthand, are especially guarded against the regime and harbor no illusions about that country whatsoever. Thus, as long as Hong Kong is free of Chinese meddling, its strategic location and international standing can provide an effective check on the ambitions of an authoritarian and increasing belligerent China.<br />\n<br />\nAs many of you know, China is well-known to skirt well-established international protocols and conventions, posing a grave threat to not only its neighbors but to the world. Recently, it has been confirmed that China has been actively stealing state secrets, engaging in corporate espionage and sabotage, and propping up anti-democratic regimes in order to advance its own agenda at the expense of the American people. As current FBI Director Christopher Wray has testified in front of Congress, almost every single recent case of intellectual property theft in the US can be traced back to China.<br />\n<br />\nUnfortunately, President Donald Trump has been reluctant to openly criticize such assaults on democratic values. Puzzlingly, he has instead suggested that President Xi Jinping of China had &quot;acted responsibly&quot;, calling for Hong Kong and China to &quot;resolve&quot; the matter themselves, thereby shrugging off any recommendation to intervene.<br />\n<br />\nYet, not all is lost. Here, we thank the Congressional-Executive Commission on China, led by Sen. Marco Rubio (R-FL) and Rep. Jim McGovern (D-MA), for introducing the Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act (H.R. 3289; S.1838). We also thank Secretary of State Mike Pompeo and various congressional leaders for bringing the plight of Hong Kong into the international spotlight and calling for the protection of democracy and basic human rights there.<br />\n<br />\nThe US has long been viewed as the beacon of freedom. We will be immensely disappointed if our faithful allies in Hong Kong are left to stand alone while fighting for US interests and security. If we do not act immediately and decisively to curb the authoritarian excesses and expansionist appetite of China, the Chinese regime might interpret this inaction as weakness and acquiescence, which will surely encourage more direct challenges on US-established rules and norms."},{"pid":"ac92b8ad44c4f8e0f10fde5288fbe1e02940ee6d","tid":1379012,"uid":36592,"like":7,"dislike":0,"score":7,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-28T17:22:32.000Z","msg":"We, therefore, call on Congress to pass the Hong Kong Human Rights and Democracy Act promptly. We also urge President Trump to be unwavering in his criticisms on China's using Hong Kong as a pawn against the US. This is the critical moment to act.<br />\n<br />\nSincerely,"},{"pid":"b2f9e6aeefcdb8cc80dfabedffa550c590bc11ff","tid":1379012,"uid":36592,"like":5,"dislike":0,"score":5,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-07-28T17:23:58.000Z","msg":"美國巴打做嘢<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n有冇人熟眾籌流程可以聯絡page 主, 一定課金<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9801e4e518004eccfe8d8435699838a21595ebf2","tid":1379012,"uid":253016,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-28T17:24:30.000Z","msg":"大大力地推"},{"pid"